2026-02-28T12:07:59.888484Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cat > /Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test/specs/001-todo-daily-focus/plan.md <<'EOF'\n# Implementation Plan: Daily Focus Todo Manager\n\n**Branch**: `001-todo-daily-focus` | **Date**: 2026-02-28 | **Spec**: [/Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test/specs/001-todo-daily-focus/spec.md](/Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test/specs/001-todo-daily-focus/spec.md)\n**Input**: Feature specification from `/specs/001-todo-daily-focus/spec.md`\n\n## Summary\n\nBuild a single-page todo manager that defaults to Daily Review mode, supports Focus mode,\nautomates end-of-day rollover and stale-item handling, and keeps an accessible trash history.\nUse a minimal-stack architecture: vanilla TypeScript + Bootstrap frontend (Vite) and a small\nNode.js API with SQLite storage in the project folder.\n\n## Technical Context\n\n**Language/Version**: TypeScript 5.x (frontend and backend), Node.js 22 LTS  \n**Primary Dependencies**: Vite, Bootstrap 5, Express, better-sqlite3, Vitest, Playwright  \n**Storage**: SQLite database file at `./data/todo.db` in repository root  \n**Testing**: Vitest (unit/integration), Playwright (end-to-end UI), Supertest (API integration)  \n**Target Platform**: Local desktop browser (latest Chrome/Firefox/Safari) with local Node runtime  \n**Project Type**: web application (single-page frontend + local API backend)  \n**Performance Goals**: Daily Review and Focus views load in <2s for p95 with up to 2,000 items  \n**Constraints**: Vanilla TypeScript UI, Bootstrap components, minimum additional libraries, no nested items  \n**Scale/Scope**: Single-user personal usage; thousands of items retained long-term including trash history\n\n## Constitution Check\n\n*GATE: Must pass before Phase 0 research. Re-check after Phase 1 design.*\n\n- **Code Quality Gate**: PASS\n  - ESLint + TypeScript strict mode + Prettier required in CI.\n  - Service/repository boundaries and explicit error handling required.\n- **Testing Gate**: PASS\n  - Tests planned for lifecycle rules, mode transitions, API behavior, and UI flows.\n  - CI gate requires all unit/integration/e2e suites passing.\n- **UX Consistency Gate**: PASS\n  - Two explicit modes with consistent status rendering (normal/completed/stale/trashed).\n  - Bootstrap components and shared state badges keep visual language consistent.\n- **Performance Gate**: PASS\n  - Performance budget defined (<2s p95 for core views, 2,000 items).\n  - Validation included in quickstart and automated test scenario.\n\n## Project Structure\n\n### Documentation (this feature)\n\n```text\nspecs/001-todo-daily-focus/\n├── plan.md\n├── research.md\n├── data-model.md\n├── quickstart.md\n├── contracts/\n│   └── todo-api.yaml\n└── tasks.md\n```\n\n### Source Code (repository root)\n\n```text\nbackend/\n├── src/\n│   ├── api/\n│   ├── db/\n│   ├── services/\n│   └── models/\n└── tests/\n\nfrontend/\n├── src/\n│   ├── components/\n│   ├── pages/\n│   ├── services/\n│   └── styles/\n└── tests/\n\ndata/\n└── todo.db\n```\n\n**Structure Decision**: Use web application split (`frontend/` + `backend/`) to keep the SPA\nimplementation simple while allowing true SQLite file persistence in the project folder.\n\n## Complexity Tracking\n\n| Violation | Why Needed | Simpler Alternative Rejected Because |\n|-----------|------------|-------------------------------------|\n| Separate backend for SPA | Browser cannot directly manage project-local SQLite reliably | Pure frontend with localStorage cannot satisfy SQLite requirement |\nEOF","workdir":"/Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test"} thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5
2026-02-28T12:08:22.877989Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"mkdir -p /Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test/specs/001-todo-daily-focus/contracts","workdir":"/Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test"} thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5
2026-02-28T12:08:22.907982Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cat > /Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test/specs/001-todo-daily-focus/research.md <<'EOF'\n# Phase 0 Research: Daily Focus Todo Manager\n\n## Decision 1: Single-page frontend with local Node API\n- **Decision**: Implement a Vite-powered SPA in vanilla TypeScript and serve data via a minimal Express API.\n- **Rationale**: Meets single-page requirement while keeping SQLite in the project folder and minimizing client complexity.\n- **Alternatives considered**:\n  - Browser-only SPA + localStorage: rejected because it does not satisfy SQLite requirement.\n  - Browser-only SPA + SQLite WASM: rejected due to larger dependency/runtime complexity and file persistence constraints.\n\n## Decision 2: SQLite access strategy\n- **Decision**: Use `better-sqlite3` with a single file `data/todo.db` created at startup.\n- **Rationale**: Minimal dependency count, synchronous API is simple and reliable for single-user local workload.\n- **Alternatives considered**:\n  - `sqlite3` async driver: rejected due to more boilerplate and callback complexity.\n  - ORM layer: rejected to keep dependency surface and abstraction overhead low.\n\n## Decision 3: Time-based lifecycle processing\n- **Decision**: Trigger lifecycle recalculation (stale marking, auto-trash eligibility) at app startup and on explicit end-of-day rollover action.\n- **Rationale**: Deterministic behavior that is easy to test and avoids background scheduling complexity.\n- **Alternatives considered**:\n  - Cron/background worker: rejected as unnecessary for local single-user app.\n  - Real-time timers per item: rejected due to state complexity and potential drift.\n\n## Decision 4: Minimal library UI approach\n- **Decision**: Use Bootstrap components for layout/forms/list groups and plain TypeScript modules for state and rendering.\n- **Rationale**: Matches user request for straightforward UI and minimum libraries.\n- **Alternatives considered**:\n  - React/Vue/Svelte: rejected as unnecessary framework overhead for this scope.\n\n## Decision 5: Testing strategy aligned to constitution\n- **Decision**: Use Vitest for domain/service logic, Supertest for API integration, and Playwright for end-to-end flows.\n- **Rationale**: Covers logic, API contract, and UX flow with minimal but complete stack.\n- **Alternatives considered**:\n  - Unit tests only: rejected because lifecycle and mode behavior need integration/e2e verification.\n  - Cypress instead of Playwright: rejected to reduce tooling variety and keep a single modern e2e stack.\nEOF","workdir":"/Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test"} thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5
2026-02-28T12:08:22.932487Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cat > /Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test/specs/001-todo-daily-focus/data-model.md <<'EOF'\n# Data Model: Daily Focus Todo Manager\n\n## InboxPoint\n- **Purpose**: Captures raw planning thoughts before conversion to todos.\n- **Fields**:\n  - `id` (UUID/string)\n  - `text` (non-empty string, max 500 chars)\n  - `created_at` (datetime)\n  - `updated_at` (datetime)\n  - `archived` (boolean; default false)\n- **Validation**:\n  - `text` required and trimmed.\n- **Relationships**:\n  - One-to-many with `TodoItem`.\n\n## TodoItem\n- **Purpose**: Actionable task tracked through inbox, daily list, completion, stale, and trash lifecycle.\n- **Fields**:\n  - `id` (UUID/string)\n  - `inbox_point_id` (nullable foreign key to InboxPoint)\n  - `title` (non-empty string, max 300 chars)\n  - `status` (enum: `INBOX`, `DAILY`, `COMPLETED`, `TRASH`)\n  - `is_stale` (boolean)\n  - `created_at` (datetime)\n  - `updated_at` (datetime)\n  - `daily_assigned_at` (nullable datetime)\n  - `completed_at` (nullable datetime)\n  - `stale_marked_at` (nullable datetime)\n  - `trashed_at` (nullable datetime)\n  - `last_activity_at` (datetime; updated on content or state changes)\n- **Validation**:\n  - `title` required and trimmed.\n  - `status` transitions must follow allowed state transitions.\n- **Relationships**:\n  - Optional many-to-one to `InboxPoint`.\n\n## DailySession\n- **Purpose**: Represents per-day focus selection context.\n- **Fields**:\n  - `session_date` (date, primary key)\n  - `mode` (enum: `REVIEW`, `FOCUS`)\n  - `created_at` (datetime)\n  - `updated_at` (datetime)\n- **Validation**:\n  - One session record per calendar date.\n\n## State Transition Rules\n- `INBOX -> DAILY`: user assigns item to today's list.\n- `DAILY -> COMPLETED`: user checks item complete.\n- `COMPLETED -> DAILY`: user unchecks item before rollover.\n- `DAILY/COMPLETED -> INBOX`: unfinished or reopened items returned on end-of-day rollover.\n- `INBOX/DAILY/COMPLETED -> TRASH`: stale and unchanged for additional 7 days.\n- `TRASH`: terminal active state; item remains accessible indefinitely.\n\n## Derived Lifecycle Flags\n- **Stale by inbox age**: `status = INBOX` and `created_at <= now - 7 days`.\n- **Stale by incomplete todo age**: `status in (DAILY, COMPLETED?)` with not completed for `>= 3 days` from `daily_assigned_at` and not in trash.\n- **Auto-trash eligible**: `is_stale = true` and `last_activity_at <= now - 7 days`.\nEOF","workdir":"/Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test"} thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5
2026-02-28T12:08:45.721200Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cat > /Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test/specs/001-todo-daily-focus/contracts/todo-api.yaml <<'EOF'\nopenapi: 3.0.3\ninfo:\n  title: Daily Focus Todo API\n  version: 0.1.0\nservers:\n  - url: http://localhost:3000\npaths:\n  /api/app-state:\n    get:\n      summary: Get current app state for the active day\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: App state payload\n  /api/inbox-points:\n    get:\n      summary: List inbox points\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Inbox points list\n    post:\n      summary: Create inbox point\n      requestBody:\n        required: true\n      responses:\n        '201':\n          description: Created\n  /api/todos:\n    get:\n      summary: List todos with optional status filter\n      parameters:\n        - in: query\n          name: status\n          schema:\n            type: string\n            enum: [INBOX, DAILY, COMPLETED, TRASH]\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Todo list\n    post:\n      summary: Create todo item\n      requestBody:\n        required: true\n      responses:\n        '201':\n          description: Created\n  /api/todos/{todoId}:\n    patch:\n      summary: Update todo content or status\n      parameters:\n        - in: path\n          name: todoId\n          required: true\n          schema:\n            type: string\n      requestBody:\n        required: true\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Updated\n        '404':\n          description: Not found\n  /api/daily-list/{todoId}:\n    put:\n      summary: Assign todo to daily list\n      parameters:\n        - in: path\n          name: todoId\n          required: true\n          schema:\n            type: string\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Assigned\n    delete:\n      summary: Remove todo from daily list\n      parameters:\n        - in: path\n          name: todoId\n          required: true\n          schema:\n            type: string\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Removed\n  /api/mode:\n    put:\n      summary: Set active mode (REVIEW or FOCUS)\n      requestBody:\n        required: true\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Mode updated\n  /api/rollover:\n    post:\n      summary: Execute end-of-day rollover\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Rollover applied\n  /api/trash:\n    get:\n      summary: List trashed items\n      responses:\n        '200':\n          description: Trash list\ncomponents:\n  schemas:\n    InboxPoint:\n      type: object\n      required: [id, text, created_at, updated_at]\n      properties:\n        id: { type: string }\n        text: { type: string }\n        created_at: { type: string, format: date-time }\n        updated_at: { type: string, format: date-time }\n    TodoItem:\n      type: object\n      required: [id, title, status, is_stale, created_at, updated_at, last_activity_at]\n      properties:\n        id: { type: string }\n        inbox_point_id: { type: string, nullable: true }\n        title: { type: string }\n        status:\n          type: string\n          enum: [INBOX, DAILY, COMPLETED, TRASH]\n        is_stale: { type: boolean }\n        created_at: { type: string, format: date-time }\n        updated_at: { type: string, format: date-time }\n        daily_assigned_at: { type: string, format: date-time, nullable: true }\n        completed_at: { type: string, format: date-time, nullable: true }\n        stale_marked_at: { type: string, format: date-time, nullable: true }\n        trashed_at: { type: string, format: date-time, nullable: true }\n        last_activity_at: { type: string, format: date-time }\nEOF","workdir":"/Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test"} thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5
2026-02-28T12:08:45.721547Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cat > /Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test/specs/001-todo-daily-focus/quickstart.md <<'EOF'\n# Quickstart: Daily Focus Todo Manager\n\n## Prerequisites\n- Node.js 22+\n- npm 10+\n\n## Setup\n1. Install dependencies.\n2. Initialize SQLite database file at `data/todo.db`.\n3. Start backend and frontend dev servers.\n\n## Validation Scenarios\n\n### 1. Daily Review default\n1. Open the app.\n2. Verify Daily Review mode is active.\n3. Add at least two inbox points.\n\nExpected: Daily Review is the default and points are listed.\n\n### 2. Build today's list and focus\n1. Create todos from inbox points.\n2. Assign selected todos to today's daily list.\n3. Switch to Focus mode.\n4. Mark one todo complete.\n\nExpected: Focus mode shows only daily-list todos; completed item stays visible with strikethrough.\n\n### 3. End-of-day rollover\n1. Keep at least one daily item unfinished.\n2. Trigger rollover endpoint/action.\n\nExpected: Unfinished items move to top of inbox.\n\n### 4. Stale and auto-trash\n1. Seed item ages so one inbox item is >7 days old and one todo is incomplete for >=3 days.\n2. Load the app.\n3. Confirm both are marked red.\n4. Advance unchanged stale item age by additional 7 days and trigger rollover.\n\nExpected: Eligible stale item moves to trash and remains visible in trash view.\n\n### 5. Performance budget\n1. Seed 2,000 total items across statuses.\n2. Load Daily Review and Focus views repeatedly (>=30 runs).\n\nExpected: p95 load time for each core view is <2s.\n\n## Test Commands\n- Unit/integration tests: run Vitest suite.\n- API integration tests: run Supertest-backed backend tests.\n- End-to-end tests: run Playwright scenarios covering review/focus/rollover/trash flows.\nEOF","workdir":"/Users/valeriy/Projects/speckit-test"} thread_id=019ca410-fbfa-7f13-be33-f83185c604c5
